<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Reportage on Economic Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1702225594 </F>
<F P=103> PY1702225594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Bolivia through 17 February: 
  The Inter-American Development Bank, IDB, will grant Bolivia 
a $100 million loan to build houses this year. (Santa Cruz EL 
MUNDO in Spanish 9 Feb 94 p 1) 
  Bolivian Government Oil Deposits President Mauricio Gonzales 
on 8 February reported that the company's revenues in 1993 
totaled 2.882 billion bolivianos and had a deficit of 82 million 
bolivianos. (La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 9 Feb 94 Economic and 
Business Section p 1) 
  On 8 February, IDB President Enrique Iglesias and Bolivian 
Ambassador Andres Petricevic signed in Washington a $64 million 
loan agreement that will be designed to implement urban 
development and cleanup projects. The World Banks also approved 
a $42 million credit to finance municipal development projects. 
(La Paz HOY in Spanish 9 Feb 94 p 6) 

</TEXT>

