<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Again Denies President Aspirations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1702233894 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1702233894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Claudia Moreira from Brasilia] </F>
  [Text] Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso again 
said that he is not a candidate for president of the Republic in 
the 1994 elections. He made this remark after President Itamar 
Franco said he will support Cardoso if he decided to become a 
candidate: 
  [Begin Cardoso recording] The president is very generous, 
polite, and noble, but this does not mean the launching of any 
candidacy at all. [end recording] 
  Minister Cardoso is now totally dedicated to the approval, 
in 
a second round of voting, of the social emergency fund bill 
that will be voted on in the plenary hall on 23 February. 

</TEXT>

