<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Activity Reportage </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1702225094 </F>
<F P=103> PY1702225094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Brazil through 17 February: 
  The Sao Paulo State Federation of Industries reported that 
the unemployment rate in Sao Paulo rose for the fourth 
consecutive month in January with the dismissal of 11,939 
workers, a drop of 0.51 percent compared with December 1993. The 
unemployment rate dropped 0.57 percent in the past 12 months, 
which represents 13,453 dismissed workers. (Sao Paulo FOLHA DE 
SAO PAULO in Portuguese 9 Feb 94 Section 2 p 1) 
  Sugar exports registered a record increase of 42.7 percent 
in 
1993 with revenues of $773 million, compared with $540 million 
in 1992. The volume of export increased from 2 million metric 
tons to nearly 3 million metric tons. (Sao Paulo GAZETA 
MERCANTIL in Portuguese 12 Feb 94 p 13) 

</TEXT>

