<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Activity Reportage </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1702211294 </F>
<F P=103> PY1702211294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Paraguay through 17 February: 
  The River Plate Basin Development Fund granted Paraguay a 
$50 
million loan, of which $30 million will be used to pave the San 
Ignacio-Pilar highway and $20 million to create an industrial 
development fund to finance industrial activities. (Asuncion HOY 
in Spanish 5 Feb 94 p 22) 
  The Paraguayan trade balance registered a $524 million 
deficit in 1993, with exports at $748 million and imports at 
$1.272 billion. This represents a drop of 10 percent compared 
with the 1992 deficit of $580 million. (Asuncion ABC COLOR in 
Spanish 13 Feb 94 p 25) 
  The Central Bank's net international reserves totaled $698.4 
million in 1993, an increase of 14.4 percent compared with 
$610.5 million in 1992. (Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 15 Feb 94 
p 13) 

</TEXT>

