<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Changes Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1702191494 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1831 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1702191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Newspaper of the Airwaves" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Alberto Fujimori has just sworn in the 
members of the cabinet presided over by Foreign Relations 
Minister Efrain Goldenberg Schreiber, new president of the 
Council of Ministers, here at the El Dorado Room in the 
government palace. The new ministers are: Dr. Jorge Trelles, 
minister of education; Dr. Liliana Canales, minister of 
industry, tourism, integration and international trade 
negotiations minister; and Engineer Raul Vittor Alfaro, minister 
of the presidency. 
  Other ministers who were ratified also took the oath of 
office. They are: Major General Victor Malca Villanueva, 
minister of defense; Maj. Gen. Juan Briones Davila, minister of 
the interior; Eng. Daniel Hokama, minister of energy and mines; 
Dr. Augusto Antonioli Vasquez, minister of labor and social 
promotion; Dr. Dante Cordova Blanco, minister of transportation, 
communications, housing, and construction; Dr. Jaimne 
Freundt-Thurne Oyanguren, minister of public health. The other 
ministers will take the oath of office at a later date because 
they are currently out of the country. They are: Eng. Jorge 
Camet, minister of economy and finance; Dr. Fernando Vega 
Santagadea, minister of justice; and Mr. Jaime Sobero Taira, 
minister of fisheries. Eng. Absalon Vasquez Villanueva, 
minister of agriculture, will also be sworn in at a later date 
because he is on a working tour of the interior. 

</TEXT>

