<H3> <TI>   Government Appoints New IDB, Social Development Head </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1602183394 </F>
<F P=103> PY1602183394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Lima LA REPUBLICA on 31 January 
publishes on page 8 a 250-word unattributed article entitled 
"Appointment of Estela as Foncodes Executive Director 
Officialized." 
  The article says the government published on 30 January a 
supreme resolution making official the appointment of Manuel 
Estela Benavidez as Peruvian representative to the 
Inter-American Development Bank and as new executive director of 
the National Compensation and Social Development Fund, Foncodes, 
replacing Arturo Woodman Pollit. 
  The article further notes that Estela will coordinate the 
technical assistance provided by international organizations, 
and Foncodes also will handle IMF and World Bank funds. 

</TEXT>

