<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Camacho Solis Announces Begining of Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1702174994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1726 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1702174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, Chiapas State, Mexico, 
17 Feb (EFE) -- Manuel Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace and 
reconciliation in Chiapas, announced today that the dialogue 
between the rebel Zapatist National Liberation Army (EZLN) and 
the government will begin next Monday at 1100 (1700 GMT). 
  Camacho Solis declined to reveal the site of the meeting, 
but 
it is believed to be in a Chiapas city, not in the jungle. 
Camacho Solis said he will spend Sunday gathering all the 
Zapatist representatives. 

