<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   OAS Concludes Special Session Ahead of Schedule </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1802211694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2019 GMT 18 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1802211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 18 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- Mexican Foreign 
Relations Secretary Manuel Tello and OAS Secretary General Joao 
Baena Soares today declared the adjournment of the 20th OAS 
special session. The meeting, which began here yesterday, was 
originally scheduled to close tomorrow following six plenary 
meetings, but the session's conclusion was unexpectedly moved 
forward. 
  During the closure announcement, information concerning an 
agreement entitled "Framework of Policies and Priorities for 
Unified Cooperation for Development" was released, which was 
signed by the 34 countries attending the session. There was no 
official explanation on why the agenda was changed, which 
reliable sources attributed only to a "time adjustment." 

</TEXT>

