<H3> <TI>   More Severe Punishment for Crossing at Guantanamo Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2002202994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2002202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jose Raul Amaro, the president of the People's 
Supreme Tribunal, released details of ruling No. 104 of 1994 for 
Guantanamo Province, which stipulates strict sanctions against 
anyone attempting to leave the country illegally through the 
border with the Yankee base in Caimaneras. According to reporter 
Leonel Perez Moya, who is in Guantanamo, the president of the 
People's Supreme Tribunal stated that the new legislation 
establishes policies for the imposition of more severe 
sanctions, although such severity will be be effected within the 
framework of the law without neglecting procedural guarantees. 
  Amaro Salup stated that they are not trying to repress for 
the sake of repression but to dissuade and protect people who 
commit this serious crime, as well as to ensure the safety of 
the border guards and the integrity of national territory. 

</TEXT>

