<DOCNO> FBIS3-33180 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat035_a_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-035 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sao Paulo Researchers Sign Scientific Cooperation Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1802143894 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1802143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the State Committee for Economic 
Cooperation and of the Sao Paulo Foundation for Support of 
Research, have signed in this capital a technical-scientific 
cooperation agreement. 
  The document was signed by Ernesto Melendez, minister 
president of the State Committee for Economic Cooperation; 
Roberto Rivas, director of the America Department of the State 
Committee for Economic Cooperation; Roberto Muller, secretary of 
the Sao Paulo Science, Technology, and Economic Development 
Department; and Jose Roberto Perez [name as heard], science 
director of the Brazilian institute. 
  For three years the two parties will contribute to promoting 
cooperation in all areas of science and technology. They also 
agreed to extend invitations to researchers and technology 
experts to participate in the research processes and as 
lecturers in scientific conferences. 

</TEXT>

