<H3> <TI>   Havana City Province MTT Begins Training </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2102030694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2102030694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 1994 training period for the Territorial Troops 
Militia [MTT] began today in Havana City Province. Habana del 
Este Municipality attained the Defense-Ready, Phase II banner, 
after winning first place in the overall emulative competion 
last year and an assessment of good during last December's 
Minfar [Ministry of the Revolutionary Armed Forces] inspection. 
(Armando Malpica), first secretary of the Communist Party of 
Cuba in the province and president of the Municipal Defense 
Council, congratulated the militiamen for having contributed to 
Habana del Este's becoming the first municipality in the 
capital, and the eighth in the nation, to achieve such an 
important status. 
  During the ceremony held on the esplanade of the Villa 
Panamericana, a group of militiamen received the Order of 
Ignacio Agramonte, Grades I and III, as well as the FAR's 23 de 
Agosto and Distinguished Service medals. 
  In the closing speech, Mayor Pedro Chavez called on 
residents 
of the capital to make a special effort this year in building 
civil defense tunnels and preparing the theater of operations. 

</TEXT>

