<H3> <TI>   Rizo Presides Over Eastern Army Training Ceremony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1602235794 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2224 GMT 
16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1602235794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The training year was begun at a large tank unit in 
Camaguey with a military review presided over by Julian Rizo, a 
Politburo member and president of the Camaguey Province Defense 
Council. Rizo earlier viewed an exhibit of the tank unit's means 
for defensive combat, communications, and production. The latter 
included the troops' food self-sufficiency supply capabilities, 
based on their own agricultural-livestock self-management. 
  At the ceremony, Colonel Jose Pina Perez discussed the work 
to be undertaken, with a view to maintaining the unit's high 
combat readiness. The unit has been a National Vanguard unit for 
(?three) consecutive years, and is a great FAR [Revolutionary 
Armed Forces] (?forward) unit. 
  Julian Rizo acknowledged the progress made by the unit's 
officers, noncommissioned officers, and enlisted men in 
achieving prestige within the Eastern Army, as well as, in this 
new year, the perfection of dexterity and command of the 
material. 

