<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Self-Employment Brings Matanzas 5.25 Million Pesos </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1802233794 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2045 GMT 
18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1802233794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Matanzas, over 8,000 people are self-employed 
under Decree Law No. 141; 61 percent of these are new requests. 
The occupations most requested to date in Matanzas Province are 
wagon worker and preparer of light foods -- the latter of which 
has been temporarily suspended. Independently of the services 
and needs of the Matanzas market that the province's residents 
might meet through self-employment, the state budget also 
benefits, receiving income of over 0.25 million pesos for new 
registrations and almost 5 million pesos in taxes. 

</TEXT>

