<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senen Casas Praises Eastern Provinces Recovery Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1902025094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1902025094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 18 February, Division General Senen Casas, a 
member of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba, 
praised the progress of the people of Guantanamo Province in 
overcoming the damage caused by severe rains in November. Casas 
Regueiro heads a ministerial commission which includes the heads 
of the Construction and Water Resources Ministries, the Cuban 
Institute of Radio and Television, and the construction 
materials industry. Their visit, which concluded at noon today, 
included socioeconomic projects in Guantanamo and Caimaneras 
Municipalities and farming areas of San Antonio del Sur 
Municipality. 
  Div. Gen. Senen Casas told reporters that the two months 
since the commission's last visit show significant progress in 
recovery efforts and demonstrate the extraordinary efforts of 
Guantanamo and Santiago de Cuba construction workers despite 
supply shortages. 
  Senen Casas, who is also the transportation minister, 
relayed 
kudos to the people of Guantanamo on behalf of Commander in 
Chief Fidel Castro; Raul Castro, minister of the Revolutionary 
Armed Forces; and the government for the progress they have 
achieved in such a short time; however, there is still much to 
be done. The ministerial commission oversaw the level of 
fulfillment of the recovery effort and the prioritized 
socioeconomic program undertaken following the Politburo 
committee's visit of April 1992. 

</TEXT>

