<H3> <TI>   Late Start for Official Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2102191194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1803 GMT 21 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2102191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, 21 Feb (Notimex) -- The 
dialogue between Manuel Camacho Solis, peace commissioner for 
the southeastern State of Chiapas, and 19 delegates from the 
Zapatist National Liberation Army began here today two hours 
late. 
  The parties began the official talks in private at 1100 
(1700 
GMT) at the San Cristobal cathedral under strict security 
measures and with the mediation of Bishop Samuel Ruiz, according 
to a spokesman for the bishop. Francisco Hernandez, spokesman 
for the diocese, added that a news conference will be held at 
1800 (0000 GMT) at the cathedral, which is being guarded by 
military police, nongovernment organizations, as well as the 
Mexican and international Red Cross. 

