<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on La Cantuta Case Developments </TI></H3>
<H4>   Military Spokesman Cited </H4>
<F P=102> PA1802192994 Paris AFP in Spanish 1605 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1802192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 18 Feb (AFP) -- A military spokesperson 
announced today that the Supreme Council of Military Justice 
(CSJM) began trying the 11 soldiers charged with the 
disappearance and deaths of a professor and nine students of La 
Cantuta University. The trial is being held behind closed doors 
and strict security measures are being observed. 
  CSJM Secretary Major Alvaro Castro told the press that the 
CSJM ordered the transfer of the prisoners to the Simon Bolivar 
Garrison where the trial will be conducted. This was done last 
night. The press will be denied access to the trial and only 
civilian lawyers will be allowed entry. 

</TEXT>

