<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Trafficker `El Vaticano' Given Life Sentence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2002033694 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2002033694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Global TV News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] According to an official communique issued by the 
Supreme Military Justice Council, Demetrio Chavez Penaherrera, 
alias El Vaticano, Peru's most powerful drug trafficker, was 
sentenced today by a military court to life imprisonment. He 
will serve this sentence at the Callao Naval Base where he will 
be Abimael Guzman's neighbor. 
  According to a document circulated today by the Supreme 
Military Justice Council, Chavez was sentenced to life and will 
serve it at the maximum security prison at the Callao Naval 
Base, possibly in a cell next to or near terrorist leader 
Abimael Guzman Reynoso. 
  Demetrio Limonier Chavez Penaherrera, alias El Vaticano, has 
been condemned for treason against the fatherland and the state, 
but he will be tried for illegal drug trafficking in a civilian 
court. El Vaticano, however, will not go the Justice Palace 
offices. Instead, the penal judge will go to the naval base 
installations just as has already been done once, according to 
information given by a military spokesmen. 
  El Vaticano was captured in Cali, Colombia, where he was 
living. According to what has been established, however, he 
continued handling the drug business in the Peruvian jungle. 
The criminal, who is now serving a life sentence, was 
considered Peru's most powerful drug trafficker due to the 
amount of drugs he collected and shipped to Colombia to be 
converted into cocaine for subsequent shipment to the U.S. and 
European markets. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

