<H3> <TI>   Venezuelan Consul Comments on Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2002154694 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1505 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2002154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Eugenio Correa] </F>
  [Text] Medellin -- Carlos Gottberg Rivero, Venezuela's 
consul general in Medellin, told the Emisoras Caracol Network 
that he is surprised at the attitude of the terrorists who this 
morning destroyed the Venezuelan diplomatic facility in Medellin. 
  [Begin Rivero recording] My first impression is one of 
surprise, because we are a neighboring country. Venezuela is a 
country that shares common interests with Colombia, a good many 
Colombians live peacefully in Venezuela and many Venezuelans 
live in Colombia under conditions of stability and respect. I 
do not have the slightest idea why the terrorists chose to bomb 
this consulate. [end recording] 
  Rivero said the terrorist attacks may be an effort to create 
chaos in the city and to hinder investigations. 
  The Venezuelan consulate in Medellin must be transferred to 
another site due to the magnitude of the damage caused by the 
bomb explosion at 0548 this morning. 

</TEXT>

