<H3> <TI>   Rebels Threaten To Kill Anyone Who Votes in Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2002165894 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2002165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guerrillas have threatened to kill residents of 12 
Santander municipalities if they attempt to participate in the 
coming elections. 
  The guerrillas' plan to prevent the election process has 
been 
expanded to eastern Santander Department, where the subversives 
have intimidated voters in rural areas. Voter lists were 
destroyed in the area's municipalities and a warning was issued: 
No one will be allowed to go to the voting sites. 
  In the 12 municipalities where guerrilla raids have taken 
place, the rebels have warned that they will control highways 
until election day and will close the area to visiting political 
candidates. 
  The area where the death threat against voters has been made 
includes the municipalities of Surata, Chata, Matanzas, and 
Veta, all of them in eastern Santander, Santa Elena, [words 
indistinct], and Pata, where police have not been allowed to 
enter, and the entire province of Velez, where the guerrillas 
threaten to kill any candidates who attempt to visit the area. 
On Monday the mayors will present a report on the situation to 
the defense minister and the Army commander. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

