<H3> <TI>   Guerrillas Attack Targets on Outskirts of Bogota </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2102031294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2102031294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Two guerrilla attacks hit the outskirts of Bogota. 
In Pasca in the southeast and in Guasca in the northeast the 
Simon Bolivar National Guerrilla Coordinating Board [CNGSB] 
attacked toll booths, communications antennas, and police 
stations. Just hours ago rebels from the 22d Front of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia [FARC] launched 
simultaneous attacks against police stations in Aguaditas and 
Pasca and a toll booth in Alto de San Miguel, Cundinamarca. At 
2130 [0330 GMT] 40 subversives from the Juan de La Cruz Front 
took positions in houses. They shot rockets and hurled grenades 
at the Aguaditas police station. For two hours four policemen 
faced the attack. 
  [Begin unidentified policeman recording] They arrived in a 
pickup truck and began shooting. Fortunately, my comrades and I 
did not panic and were able to face the situation. As you can 
see, we came through it without injuries. [end recording] 
  Meanwhile, another small group of the 22d FARC Front 
dynamited the Alto de San Miguel toll booth. 
  [Begin unidentified employee recording] They arrived at 
about 2100 and made us move our personnel away from the 
building, where they were collecting the toll payments. Then 
they blew up the installations. [end recording] 
  The authorities also reported that 60 rebels destroyed the 
Pasca police station. Seven policemen held off the attackers 
for eight hours. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

