<H3> <TI>   Security Meetings Held on Guerrilla Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2102193094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1738 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2102193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Guerrilla activities have caused special security 
council meetings to be held today in several cities throughout 
the country. Government Minister Fabio Villegas traveled to 
Santander to preside over a Ministers Council meeting where 
electoral guarantees for Boyaca, Santander and Norte de 
Santander Departments would be discussed. 
  In Bucaramanga, the Democracy Plan has been presented in the 
presence of the government minister, the commander of the 
military forces, governors, and police commanders from the area 
of the Army's 2d Division. Alvaro Salgar, governor of Santander 
del Norte Department, said the following: 
  [Begin Salgar recording] We hope to support election day. We 
hope to have an airplane available to transport units to the 
many voting areas and also a couple helicopters for any 
emergencies. [end recording] 
  Although the subversives have announced a plan to sabotage 
the elections, state forces have guaranteed that they will be at 
all the voting centers. Members of the National Civil Registry 
Office are also participating in the meeting. They will 
establish which voting tables will have the most dangers, which 
will allow them to provide the required security for the 
upcoming elections. The Democracy Plan will also be presented 
this afternoon in Yopal, Casanare. 

</TEXT>

