<H3> <TI>   Government Minister Notes Protection for Candidates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2102144194 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2102144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Caracol 0600 to 0900" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- Government Minister Fabio 
Villegas Ramirez, in pointing out his concern for the escalation 
of terrorism over the weekend, when subversives perpetrated a 
number of actions in Antioquia, Meta, Arauca, Cundinamarca, and 
Tolima Departments, has said the government has not been weak in 
maintaining public order in the country but that it is 
implementing measures to give adequate protection to those are 
working in the current electoral process. 
  Villegas reported on the protection provided for candidates 
to government positions but admitted that many of them do not 
want to be subjected to this type of control. 

</TEXT>

