<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Start; Land Grants Proposed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2102134994 Managua Radio Nicaragua in Spanish 1200 GMT 21 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2102134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Today, the government begins 
the first serious negotiations for a definitive cease-fire and 
the disarmament of the Northern Front 3-80's rebel troops, led 
by Jose Angel Talavera, a.k.a. El Chacal, in an effort to 
eventually pacify the country through demobilization, which will 
be the key to national stability and production. 
  Today a Nicaraguan Government commission will present a 
proposal to the rebels which includes the granting of lands and 
the legalization of ownership for the disarmed, creation of jobs 
in the community, and the implementation of educational and 
health programs. 

</TEXT>

