<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gen Ortega Says No Plans To Reestablish Draft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1902021894 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1100 GMT 18 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1902021894 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Sandino </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Events" newscast] </F>
  [Text] General Humberto Ortega has said the EPS [Sandinist 
People's Army] will not reestablish the SMP [Patriotic Military 
Service]. During the ceremony to transfer the EPS installations 
located at kilometer marker 20 of the road to Masaya to the 
Environment and Natural Resources Ministry, EPS Chief Gen. 
Humberto Ortega said yesterday that the Military High Command is 
not planning to reestablish the SMP in the country. Here is what 
Gen. Ortega said: 
  [Begin Ortega recording] It is not enough to disarm. An 
effective program is necessary to permit the disarmed 
individuals to earn a livelihood and gradually rejoin the 
country's life through employment in order to increase their 
standard of living and live decently. Disarmament is not enough 
for peace to exist. We must all work to overcome the high levels 
of inequality and poverty and to prevent the concentration of 
capital in the hands of a few people because that will always 
create a big gap between the few who have everything and the 
many who have nothing. Those are the real roots of violence that 
might come in the future. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

