<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chamorro Creates Social Communications Directorate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1802124594 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 0017 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1802124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 17 Feb (ACAN-EFE) -- Nicaraguan President 
Violeta Chamorro today appointed Luis Rivas Leiva, a physician 
and Social Democrat, to the post of director of Social 
Communications of the Presidency of the Republic. Chamorro also 
signed a decree creating the Social Communications Directorate, 
which dissolves the Public Relations and Official Information 
Directorate of the Presidency, as well as the Information and 
Press Directorate of the Presidency. 
  The Public Relations and Official Information Directorate 
was 
previously headed by Danilo Lacayo Lanzas, a lawyer and Social 
Democrat, who resigned on Tuesday to practice his profession and 
return to the private sector, according to official sources. 
  The Information and Press Directorate of the Presidency was 
in charge of reporting the activities of cabinet members and was 
headed by Ernesto Robleto, who resigned from the position in the 
latter part of 1993, also to return to the private sector. 
  Chamorro appointed journalist Maria Alicia Talavera Sevilla, 
former editor of BARRICADA newspaper in Managua, as deputy 
director of the Social Communications Directorate. Both 
officials were sworn in by the Nicaraguan president in her 
office this afternoon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

