<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Resigns, Military Appointments Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1802223594 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1802223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Teleonce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Report by Willy Melgar; from the "Telepress" newscast] 
  [Text] President Ramiro de Leon Carpio has accepted 
Government Minister Arnoldo Ortiz Moscoso's resignation, which 
was tendered yesterday. General Marco Antonio Gonzalez Taracena 
today assumed office as chief of staff of defense. He replaces 
Gen. Jose Luis Quilo Ayuzo. Gen. Carlos Enrique Pineda Carranza 
has assumed office as deputy chief of staff of defense. Arnoldo 
Balconi Turcios has assumed office as army inspector general. 
The appointment of a replacement for the government minister is 
being studied. 
  In addition, the president announced the appointment of a 
special commission to investigate the assassination of Jorge 
Carpio Nicolle. The commission will be made up of 
representatives of the Government and Defense Ministries, the 
Prosecutor General's Office, the Human Rights Ombudsman's 
Office, and the Archdiocese's Human Rights Office. 

</TEXT>

