<H3> <TI>   Two Firemen Killed, Others Injured in Grenade Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2002162294 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1538 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2002162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 20 Feb (ACAN-EFE) -- At least two 
firemen were killed and five other people injured when a grenade 
exploded at a fire station in San Lucas Sacatepequez near 
Guatemala City. 
  The Volunteer Firemen's press office told ACAN-EFE that the 
device was thrown inside the station yesterday by unidentified 
men and exploded in the hands of Noe Morales De la Rosa. 
  De la Rosa and Boris Manfredo Bonilla were killed on the 
spot. Victor Rolando Aguilar Castro, Byron Cisneros Camey, and 
three members of the Guatemalan Scout Association (Alba Ramirez, 
Emili Rodriguez and Miriam Rodriguez) were injured. 
  The Volunteer Firemen are demanding that the authorities 
investigate the attack and that its perpetrators be punished. 

</TEXT>

