<F P=103> PA2202015594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 21 Feb (EFE) -- According to press reports, 
President Sixto Duran-Ballen dismissed Ecuadoran Information 
Minister Carlos Vera Rodriguez for showing disrespect for the 
command hierarchy by criticizing Vice President Alberto Dahik. 
  The president refused to confirm or deny such reports and 
noted that it will be Vera himself who will refer to this matter 
at a news conference that he will hold tomorrow, Tuesday. 
  Vera, a well-known journalist and radio and television 
producer in his country, urged Dahik to straighten up and not 
"spread rumors." Vera made this remark after the vice president 
announced that the government is studying the possibility of 
convoking a plebiscite on topics that have not been disclosed by 
government spokesmen yet. 
  The Ecuadoran vice president was elected to that post while 
ministers get appointed. According to television, radio, and 
newspaper reports, this explains the government hierarchy. 

