<F P=103> FL2202145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] With the signing of a friendship accord with Havana 
City on 21 February, Cuba became the first Latin America country 
to conclude a cooperation agreement with Kiev. Leonid 
Kosakivsky, mayor of Kiev and envoy of the Ukrainian president, 
expressed his satisfaction with the accord, which will promote 
contacts between economic sectors, as well as the exchange of 
information and experiences in science, urban planning, 
construction, public health, the environment, culture, and 
professional education. At the ceremony last night at the former 
home of General Maximo Gomez in La Quinta de los Molinos, 
Havana, Pedro Chavez, president of the People's Administration 
Council, presented the distinguished guest award to Kosakivsky. 

