<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor Orders Arrest of Ortega's Bodyguards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2202194394 Managua Radio Sandino in Spanish 1200 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2202194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Sandino </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Events" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday, Military Prosecutor Lester Gallo ordered 
the arrest of two of Army Commander General Humberto Ortega 
Saavedra's bodyguards in connection with the investigation into 
the death of a young man by the name of Jean Paul Genie. 
  Captain Roberto Danilo Chacon Rivas and First Lieutenant 
Alejandro Cesar Lopez Rodriguez must be temporarily detained for 
10 days, while the trial is being held. Yesterday, when these 
two men appeared at the Court of the Judge Advocate to make a 
statement, the prosecutor ordered their arrest. 
  Another four of General Ortega's bodyguards are to testify 
today and tomorrow. Captain Chacon Rivas and First Lieutenant 
Lopez Rodriguez were sent to the Disciplinary Unit of the 
Sandinist People's Army on the road to Masaya. The bodyguards' 
defense attorneys have criticized the arrest order. 

</TEXT>

