<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Commander Works To Rescue Kidnapped Politicians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2202133394 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2202133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Villavicencio -- General Luis Bernardo Urbina, 7th 
Brigade Army commander, has claimed he is working earnestly to 
safely rescue Jorge Carmelo Perez Alvarado, candidate to the 
House of Representatives; Leovigildo Criollo, former San Juan de 
Arana mayor; and Jose Lozano, mayor of Puerto Rico, who were 
kidnapped by the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia this 
weekend. Gen. Rubina said the situation is worrisome, but they 
are strengthening all actions to try to deter terrorism from 
escalating and to ensure tranquility. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

