<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2202170094 </F>
<F P=103> PA2202170094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Peruvian economic developments through 22 February: 
  Through a decree published in the official government 
gazette, the Energy and Mines Ministry has officially outlined 
its agreement to guarantee and promote investments. The 
agreement's eighth clause indicates that government guarantees 
will cover 15 years, starting from the date of crediting the 
investment. Such investments must be approved by the National 
Mining Directorate. (Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 9 Feb 94) 
  The Central Reserve Bank has reported that Peru's net 
international reserves fluctuate between $1.7 and $1.8 billion. 
Those figures represent the highest reserve level in recent 
years, bank officials added. (Lima Global de Television Network 
in Spanish 0100 GMT 16 Feb 94) 

</TEXT>

