Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 18 Feb (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
allegedly held a telephone conversation with Cuban leader Fidel 
Castro. During the conversation, which lasted several minutes, 
the two leaders discussed the situation of their respective 
countries and, particularly, the commercial blockade against 
Cuba. 
  This information was published today by the Buenos Aires 
daily AMBITO FINANCIERO, which also said the contact had been 
made by a relative of Menem, of Syrian origin, who lives in 
Havana. 
  According to the press report, Menem spoke to his relative 
and after the protocol greetings, she said, "I will put you on 
to a friend" and Castro's voice appeared on the other end of the 
line. 
  Relations between Menem and Castro remain distant because 
the 
Argentine president criticizes his Cuban counterpart for not 
calling elections in the island so its inhabitants can elect 
their leaders. 

