<H3> <TI>   Perez Novoa Charges U.S. `Manipulating' Free Expression </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2302145594 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2302145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 22 February, Jose Perez Novoa, Cuban Ambassador 
in Geneva, accused the United States of manipulating freedom of 
expression with its monopoly of media outlets. During the 50th 
session of the UN Human Rights Commission, the Cuban diplomat 
gave the example of the exposure to radiation on unsuspecting 
subjects. Over a decade ago experiments were conducted on 
retarded individuals. This was only made known last month. Perez 
Novoa stressed that there are no guarantees that other human 
rights violations cases are kept quiet within the so-called 
freedom of speech of the United States. 
  The UN Human Rights Commission has yet to vote on racism and 
xenophobia, increasing phenomenons in Europe. 

</TEXT>

