<H3> <TI>   Chinese Ambassador Stresses Growing Bilateral Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2302200994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2302200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] While participating in the ceremony marking the 
fourth anniversary of the Cuban-Chinese friendship cooperative 
for agriculture and livestock production in the municipality of 
Cifuentes in Villa Clara, Chinese Ambassador to Cuba Xu Yicong 
said that bilateral relations with Cuba are developing 
satisfactorily for both countries. We have many reasons to seek 
the strengthening of Cuban-Chinese relations of friendship and 
cooperation, because the two countries have the same principles 
and ideals uniting us closely, Xu Yicong said. 
  The Chinese ambassador added that political relations 
between 
the two countries are also growing closer every day, trade is 
increasing, and economic cooperation is developing quickly. He 
said that the Joint Commission for Cuban-Chinese Cooperation 
will meet in March in Havana to study trade prospects between 
the two nations. 
  In Santa Clara, Xu Yicong visited the installation of what 
will be the largest Cuban bicycle factory with Chinese 
technology. This factory will be able to produce 150,000 units 
annually. 

</TEXT>

