<H3> <TI>   Chamber President Reports on Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2402044294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2010 GMT 20 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2402044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 20 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- Carlos Martinez 
Salsamendi, the president of the Cuban Chamber of Commerce, has 
reported here that Cuba registered more than 500 foreign 
corporations and 112 joint enterprises as of the end of 1993. 
Martinez Salsamendi said that 78 new corporations joined the 
chamber last year. He made the announcement during a meeting 
with businessmen from the Canary Islands. The business leader 
also said that 28 of the joint enterprises are engaged in 
tourism activities. 
  During the meeting, the businessmen and entrepreneurs from 
the Canary Islands expressed their interest in doing business 
with Cuba. The group is accompanying President Manuel Hermoso of 
the Government of the Canary Islands, who began a six-day 
official visit to Cuba on Friday. This is the third trip by a 
Spanish autonomous government leader to the island, following 
tours by Gallaecian President Manuel Fraga Iribarne and Asturian 
leader Juan Luis Rodriguez Vigil in 1991. 

</TEXT>

