<H3> <TI>   Central Army To Maintain Agricultural Vehicles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2402010894 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2320 GMT 
23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2402010894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Central Army is taking steps to implement the 
instructions given by the Minister of the Revolutionary Armed 
Forces to support the conservation of unused agricultural 
equipment. In this extensive territory that comprises five 
provinces, thousands of tractors and trucks that have been 
paralyzed because of the lack of fuel and spare parts or as a 
consequence of the recent transformations that have taken place 
in agricultural industry will be properly maintained to prevent 
their deterioration and to ensure operation when circumstances 
permit. Contacts have been made between delegations of the 
Ministry of Agriculture in Matanzas, Villa Clara, Cienfuegos, 
Sancti Spiritus, and Ciego de Avila, so that, in the near 
future, classes can be held to demonstrate the proper 
maintenance of agricultural equipment. 

</TEXT>

