<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chiapas Talks Continue Behind Closed Doors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2302145194 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1304 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2302145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1304 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning from Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] On Tuesday at the cathedral of San Cristobal de las 
Casas, Peace Commissioner Manuel Camacho Solis and members of 
the Zapatist National Liberation Front [EZLN] continued their 
negotiations behind closed doors. The dialogue is moving forward 
and the prospects for resolving the conflict are good. 
  At a news conference, San Cristobal Bishop Samuel Ruiz 
announced the EZLN had presented its list of demands to the 
federal government's representative, who in turn provided broad 
answers. Ruiz, however, did not disclose any of the EZLN's 
specific requests. 
  Meanwhile, Subcommander Marcos explained the reasons for his 
struggle. He criticized society for having forgotten the Indian 
community and asked society to remain at the EZLN's side. 
  When his turn came to speak, Commissioner Camacho said the 
only way to resolve Chiapas' problems is by strengthening the 
Republic's institutions. He pointed out that a peaceful solution 
for Chiapas will be found in new answers for the state, not only 
for the EZLN but for society as a whole. 

</TEXT>

