<H3> <TI>   Chilean, Paraguayan Envoys `Held Hostage' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2402005294 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2355 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2402005294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Guatemala City, 23 Feb (DPA) -- Chilean 
Ambassador to Guatemala Christian Bisquert and Paraguayan 
Ambassador to Guatemala Gilberto Caniza are being held hostage 
in the Government Palace in Guatemala City after the palace was 
occupied today by a group of union members demanding that 
President Ramiro de Leon Carpio's government increase their 
wages. 
  Along with the two diplomats, about 1,000 others are also 
being held hostage at the palace. Some 700 of these people are 
employees of various government ministries that have offices in 
the palace, and the rest were people visiting the various 
offices. The Chilean and Paraguayan ambassadors were at the 
Guatemalan Foreign Ministry, which is housed on the first floor 
of the Government Palace, when the siege began. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

