<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreements Reached </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2402030094 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 0146 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2402030094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Interview with Adolfo Reyes, Guatemalan deputy government 
minister, by Julieta Cardenas at the National Palace in 
Guatemala City--live] 
  [Text] [Cardenas] Here is a last minute report: The problem 
created by the Fenasep [National Federation of Public Employees 
Unions] leaders has begun to be solved. Deputy Government 
Minister Adolfo Reyes explains the agreements reached tonight 
inside the National Palace. Can you explain the agreements to 
our listeners? 
  [Reyes] It is fortunate that once again through dialogue-- 
without any violence and in compliance with the law and 
Constitution--we have done our work. We have met with the five 
Fenasep leaders who are here in my office. We are drafting a 
document that includes a point on the resumption of talks; this 
will take place on 1 March, starting at 1500, when the president 
will hold a special meeting with them. Other points are 
nonviolence and a revision of dialogue. They have maintained 
their request for a 40-percent salary increase. 
  In addition to the people gathered outside the main square, 
there was no violence, fortunately. The police are remaining 
watchful, protecting the people, and preventing incidents. When 
we sign this document, which we hope will be in the next 10 
minutes, the union leaders promised us they will withdraw 
peacefully. We will meet again on 1 March at 1500. That is all 
I have to say. 
  [Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in Spanish at 0155 
GMT on 24 February cites Fenasep leader Armando Sanchez as 
saying: "We are going to proceed to leave the building, because 
we reached an agreement to meet in a new process of negotiation 
with the government on 1 March."] 

</TEXT>

