<F P=102>  FL2302181994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2302181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] According to Deputy Jean Mandenave, who is 
supporting the president's stand on the possible appointment of 
a prime minister, the reactivation of the Governors Island 
agreement is the only solution. Deputy Mandenave condemns the 
international community which is putting pressure on President 
Jean-Bertrand Aristide while the Army is acting as it wishes, at 
the same time labelling the parliamentarians' trip to Washington 
as a dilatory maneuver. 
  [Begin Mandenave recording in Creole] [passage omitted] I 
remain convinced that it is necessary to have a government that 
is not a government of resignation. The current government has 
resigned. A government cannot spend all its time dealing with 
the day-to-day business of the state. But the path must be 
cleared before the president appoints a prime minister. General 
Cedras must step down first. Everybody knows that the Malval 
government failed because the Army and the Revolutionary Front 
for the Promotion and Progress of Haiti members prevented it 
from functioning. [end recording] 
  Furthermore, Deputy Mandenave says he is expecting nothing 
positive from the dismissal [corrects himself] sorry, from the 
other office of the Senate at the initiative of Sen. Dupiton. 
In the opinion of Deputy Mandenave, that is nothing more than a 
meeting between friends. [passage omitted] 

