Spanish 1200 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2302131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Edgar Gallego Rigo from Medellin; from the </F>
"Caracol 0600-0900" newscast] 
  [Text] Medellin authorities are currently investigating the 
motives and persons responsible for the explosion of 10 kg of 
dynamite early this morning in the central part of Bello, 
northern Medellin. 
  The explosion injured two policemen and caused considerable 
property damage to a local store, the police station, the 
municipal inspection department, and another municipal building. 
It also caused damage to three floors of the old municipal 
palace, 10 local commercial stores, and a fleet of nine official 
[word indistinct]. 
  The fire department is currently preparing an assessment of 
the damage caused by this terrorist attack, which has not yet 
been attributed to any group. 

</TEXT>

