<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2302174394 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 21 
Feb 94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PA2302174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Lastenia Murillo Munoz] </F>
  [Text] Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Georgiy Mamedov 
arrived in Panama yesterday at the invitation of the government 
to strengthen ties of friendship and trade between the two 
countries. Mamedov, who will remain in Panama two days, will 
meet today with President Guillermo Endara and will later meet 
with Foreign Minister Jose Raul Mulino. He will meet with the 
local and foreign media tomorrow. 
  The Russian deputy foreign minister was met at Tocumen 
International Airport by Deputy Foreign Minister Carlos Cordero 
and members of the Russian Consulate. Alexis Ermaro, Russian 
consul in Panama, said this is the first time a high-ranking 
Russian Government official has visited Panama since the Soviet 
Union was dissolved two years ago. Ermaro said the deputy 
foreign minister will also meet with Panamanian businessmen to 
study the benefits of trading with Panama. 
  The consul approved of Mamedov's visit because his 
government 
is mainly interested in the trade potential, given Panama's good 
relations with the European markets. Likewise, he said the two 
countries wish to establish technical, trade, and financial 
cooperation to strengthen those relations. The diplomat did not 
give details about the meetings or the topics that the Russian 
authorities would discuss with the Panamanian authorities during 
the two-day visit. 
  Trade relations between the two nations have gradually 
developed after the Soviet Union disappeared. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-33481 </DOCNO>
