<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consultation Protocol Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2302182894 Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 23 Feb 94 p 3A </F>
<F P=103> PA2302182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Manuel Alvarez Cedeno] </F>
  [Text] Panamanian and Russian diplomatic sources have 
disclosed that yesterday in Panama City both countries signed a 
Consultation and Opinion Exchange Protocol. The document was 
signed for Panama by Foreign Minister Jose Mulino and for the 
Russian Federation by Deputy Foreign Minister Georgiy Mamedov, 
who arrived in Panama on 20 February and returned home yesterday. 
  In the protocol the sides agreed to periodically consult and 
exchange opinions with each other on bilateral issues, common 
problems, and topics that are discussed at international forums. 
  Mamedov said the signing of the document "constitutes a 
historic moment for relations between Panama and Russia, 
especially with regard to both country's political and 
commercial prospects." The diplomat, whose words were 
officially translated into Spanish, asserted that Panama plays 
"a very important role" in his country's foreign policy, and 
added that this event "marks the beginning of our political 
relationship." 
  Panama and Russia established consular relations on 29 March 
1991. 
  Meanwhile, Mulino said the Russian diplomat's visit "is an 
unprecedented event in the history of Panamanian international 
policy because, among other things, it is the first time a 
ranking Russian official has visited our country." Mulino said 
he is certain that relations between the two countries will 
prove to be very beneficial. Regarding his meeting with Mamedov 
and President Guillermo Endara, Mulino explained that they 
discussed both countries' complex and difficult transitions to 
democracy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

